# Windsurf AI Rules — Residential Construction Gantt Manager

## Cross-IDE Awareness
This project is also edited in Anti-gravity IDE (.adal/).
- Do NOT modify files in .adal/ or .adalrules
- Check TASKS.md before starting work — tasks marked [AG] belong to Anti-gravity
- After completing work, update TASKS.md with what was done
- Do not commit changes to files Anti-gravity may be actively editing (check TASKS.md for [AG] in-progress items)

## Project Context
- Stack: React + TypeScript + Vite, Supabase backend, Vercel deployment
- Database: Supabase with RPC functions for all data access
- Scheduling engine: collision detection and constraint propagation in app/src/lib/
- Testing data: managed via scripts/testing-data.mjs and snapshots/

## Code Conventions
- Use Supabase RPC for all data access — no direct table queries from the frontend
- Follow existing file organization in app/src/components/ and app/src/lib/
- Keep scheduling engine logic isolated in app/src/lib/scheduling/

## Task Protocol
- Before starting a task, check TASKS.md for ownership tags
- Mark tasks you start with [WS] (Windsurf)
- After completing, move the task to Completed and note what was done
- Log architectural decisions in docs/decisions.md so Anti-gravity stays informed
